On the other hand, Cytochemistry is the study of intracellular distribution of chemicals, reac- tion sites, and enzymes, often by means of stain- ing reactions, radioactive isotope uptake, selec- tive metal distribution in electron microscopy, or other methods (Free Merriam-Webster Dictionary: http://www.merriam-webster.
